Dorothea Enrichment

Dorothea is a tool/database containing mouse regulons to infer TF activitiy from gene expression data. Here we use the VIPER method to enrich TF from our RNA-seq data per sample

After loading the data we replace ensembl IDs with gene symbols. We calcuate the TF sites based on the vst transformed expression values from DESeq2.

Resulting plots

The first Heatmap shows the Normalized enrichment score for each sample for all transcription factors. THe condition is given as a colored annotation at the top of the plot.

## [[1]]

The following plots show the mean density distribution of the NES for each sample group, followed by a barplot showing the top enrichment for TF activity in each sample group. The y axis shows the TF factor, the x axis the NES.
